Package edu.uiuc.ncsa.qdl.extensions

This contains the classes for extending the QDL language with Java.

See: Description

  • Interface Summary 
    Interface Description
    QDLFunction
    A wrapper for a single Java method that can be invoked from QDL.
    QDLLoader
    Interface for loading your classes.
    QDLVariable
    this represents a QDL variable.
  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    JavaModule
    This will let you create your own extensions to QDL in Java.
    QDLFunctionRecord
    This is needed for internal bookkeeping.

Package edu.uiuc.ncsa.qdl.extensions Description

This contains the classes for extending the QDL language with Java. You create a module written in Java then import it and at that point can use its functions and variables as per usual inside QDL.
